{
  "texts": [
    "In this case, the particular dynamics of S and S *, which are somewhat unpredictable especially at the outset, would likely not concern the policy-maker.In our final simulation, we vary several of the parameters (including some that were fixed in figures 3-6).",
    "Specifically, we set the birth rate to b = 0.3, the death rate to δ = 1, the infectivity rate of the disease to β = 0.5, the recovery rate for the disease to γ = 0.25, the infectivity rate for noncompliance to µ = 8, the recovery rate from noncompliance to ν = 1, and the uncertainty in the infectivity rates to σ β = σ µ = 0.125.",
    "We take ξ = 0 so that newly introduced members of the population are uniformly compliant.",
    "The reduction in infectivity is held at α = 0.25.",
    "With all these decisions, we consider the disease free state s = ν+δ µ = 1 4 and s * = b δ -ν+δ µ = 1 20."
  ]
}